Although the ceasefire granted on November 21 continues, fighting this week has strengthened supporters of force on both sides.
The leaders of Hamas, the Islamist movement that has led Gaza since 2007, will boast of forcing the Israelis to give up, even though Gaza has suffered a beating.
Having killed some of its leaders and pushed Gaza’s 1.7 million people into one of the most miserable and overcrowded corners of the planet, Israel has failed to destroy Hamas.
Indeed, Hamas is gaining ground in the West Bank, the other part of Palestine currently in the hands of its Fatah rivals, the other more moderate Palestinian faction.
In addition, Hamas leaders might think that time is their ally.
The influence of Islamists in the Arab world is growing, and Hamas has made rich and powerful friends.
