Correa took the opportunity to reaffirm himself as an advocate of press freedom and said what he did not tolerate was "mediocrity, bad faith and lies that hurt freedom of expression."
“The biggest enemies of press freedom are not malicious or perverse politicians but bad journalists paying for greed, blackmail and extortion,” he said.
